text:
My WeekView calendar thingy disables the DayView (child view) which has this color as its textColor. Does anyone know why it doesn't set the color to @color/darkRed when it's disabled?
```&lt;?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?&gt;
&lt;selector xmlns:android="http://schemas.android.com/apk/res/android"&gt;
	&lt;item android:state_enabled="false"
		android:color="@color/darkRed"/&gt;

	&lt;item android:state_selected="true"
		android:color="@color/red"/&gt;

	&lt;item android:color="@android:color/white"/&gt;
&lt;/selector&gt;```
